text: Chatham is a New England town in Barnstable County, Massachusetts. The population was 6,594 at the 2020 census. Chatham is home to the Monomoy National Wildlife Refuge, located on Monomoy, and to Monomoy Theatre. ==Other websites== * Official website Category:Towns in Massachusetts Category:1665 establishments Category:1660s establishments in Massachusetts
